"""Auto-generated brick instance data for the Kapla Tower example.

Regenerate with ``python _extract_kapla_usda.py`` from the repo
root. Source: ``KaplaTower2.usda``.

The PhoenX C# demo loads this scene from a USD ``PointInstancer``;
this module embeds the same data so the example doesn't depend on
USD or the original asset.

Conventions:
    * ``BRICK_FULL_EXTENTS``: ``(sx, sy, sz)`` full extents of the
      box prototype, ready for ``add_shape_box(hx=sx/2, ...)``.
    * ``POSITIONS``: ``(N, 3) float32`` instance translations in
      world space, +Z-up (USD's native frame).
    * ``ORIENTATIONS``: ``(N, 4) float32`` instance rotations, in
      ``(x, y, z, w)`` order (Newton / Warp convention). The USDA
      stores ``(w, x, y, z)`` -- this module already swaps to the
      Newton order so callers can feed it straight into
      ``wp.quat`` / ``wp.transform``.
"""

